content: I've now got this paid version. Which is great, aside from the snooze being a bit glitchy. I changed a setting on my phone and it now works most of the time (not completely reliable, so that's not ideal). I've added the app to the list that isn't energy saved. So far so good. There are some tones which if you've downloaded them don't have permissions to be used with this app. I got some via Zedge and none work. Bit of a shame as they worked with my last alarm app. The free version is in my opinion completely pointless as you can't change the alarm duration and so it's a one sound alarm, which is the same as my phones calendar. I'll see how this goes. The developer responds quickly and tries to help.
For some reason, only on my phone., the calendar no longer sounds an alarm. Adding new events to my calendar really doesnt work. It does not sync with my tablet anymore.
replyContent: Hi Zoey, this has probably nothing to do with app itself. Synchronization is not done by my app, but by your phone. Turning on internet and auto sync for all accounts should solve problem. Also - I do not quite understand what do you mean that adding events doesnt work - maybe write me a bit more details by mail? :) Thanks & Cheers, MS

content: I've used this app for probably 3 years and generally like it a lot.  At one point, however, it stopped sounding the alarm, so I uninstalled/reinstalled it.   It started working again, but I lost quite a few of my calendar events.   Recently it started giving me the alarm music doubled (starting about 3 seconds apart).  After a couple of weeks of that, it now gives me no sound at all.  Short of reinstalling it again, I'm not sure if there's anything else I can do.  Any suggestions?
Does what it does and does it well

content: It was great on Android 5 and 6. However with Android 7.1 you cant snooze the alarm until you have unlocked your phone and sometimes the app doesnt respect Do Not Disturb.

Love this because there are no extra steps - now all my reminders in Google calendar set of a persistent, loud alarm on my phone. I'm not glued to my phone nor do I want to check it constantly, so I need it to ring when there is an important notification. Invaluable to make sure I remember important appointments. I'm recommending this to everyone I know!
I loved this app but I got a new phone LG G4 and now it refuses to work
Responds to question and suggestions! Alarm has always worked perfectly. thank you!

Happy to support continued development of this. Would love android wear support and would also prefer to have the alarm in ADDITION to the notifications, rather than a replacement. Not sure if it's possible though. To have an alarm for some events and the standard notification for other (less important) events. Given the choice though, I'll take the alarm!

This app was recommended by a few people as a replacement for the older app "Calendar Snooze" (no longer supported). However, it is missing a few primary snooze functions: 1. No custom snooze duration, there is no way to set a snooze time longer than 60 minutes, there are times I want to snooze for a day. 2. No way to edit the original event from the app. 3. No custom setting for reminder duration, i would like to have the ability to have the reminder set for unlimited duation.
replyContent: Hi Ryan, in new update (should be available within days) I added all you wrote: 1) custom snooze durations (minutes/hours/days) 2) editing event within app 3) new reminder duration settings and also management of snoozed alarms within app and much more! Wait few days and check it, or write me mail and I can send u new version ASAP. Cheers, MS
